I love this chicken, but it is VERY garlicky...and that is why I love it! I can only cook this when I find myself dining alone because no one else in the house likes garlic as much as I do. To the cook in Apple Valley, WOW you doubled the garlic? That would be intense.

Rating: 3
This recipe is greatly improved by adding judicious amounts of saffron, flour and salt, and decreasing stock to no more than two cups. Think Spanish. Indeed, instead of flour or perhaps in addition to it, one might add pulverized almonds for a slightly different texture and taste.

Rating: 3
This was very tasty. The chicken was moist and flavorful. The sauce was very good over the garlic rice I had with it. I made it for guests and they said it was definitely a keeper recipe!

Rating: 3
I happened to have minced garlic in a jar, regular white wine instead of cognac, dried rosemary, and bottled lemon, but this still came out very nicely. Reducing the sauce is the key, and don't overcook the chicken. A definite keeper.

